The current implementation fo _hjcd_ik.py is a little slow and has numerical accuracy issues. I would like to replace them with Jax FFI external bindings. In the repository is a submodule HJCD-IK which is written in raw CUDA and uses GrID for roboti modeling. Using this as inspiration, implement a CUDA version of _hjcd_ik.py in cuda_kernels and call it as an alternative solver in _hjcd_ik.py to the Jax implementation. You can reference the forward kinematics implementation as inspiration or if you require it as a subroutine for inverse kinematics. Do not use GrID or any HJCD-IK specific dependencies. Remember to use the CUDA stream to avoid numerical instability issues.